The paper deals with the Graph Isomorphism Problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The algorithm presented in the paper is based on the degree of the input graphs, which suggests that it may also be relevant to Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Computational Geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithms and their running times, which are topics covered in Data Structures (cs.DS) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
